{
  "text": "During entomological investigations in ten randomly selected villages in a JE-endemic region of Bangladesh [CITATION_1] , birds-including chickens, ducks, and pigeons-were observed to be the most abundant domestic animals, often comprising between 50% and 100% of household animal communities. These birds are also reported to be the most numerous domestic animals by census data for the three districts where surveyed villages are located [19] .",
  "citation_candidates": [
